Phase 8: Comprehensive Logging Modernization
This phase implements a system-wide upgrade of the logging infrastructure. Every Python module will be standardized to use the centralized Forensic Logger, significantly improving the depth and traceability of system diagnostics.

User Review Required
IMPORTANT

This refactor will touch almost every Python file in the src/ directory (~63 files). While the changes are non-destructive (adding imports and standardizing log calls), it is a large-scale modification.

TIP

I will be enabling exc_info=True (full tracebacks) for all critical error blocks. This will increase log file size during failures but provides the exact "Forensic" depth required for troubleshooting.

Proposed Changes
1. Standardization Pattern
For every module, I will apply the following pattern:

Import: from src.core.logger import get_logger
Init: log = get_logger("module_basename")
Modernization: Replace logging. and print() calls with the module-specific log.
Tracebacks: Update except Exception as e: blocks to log.error(..., exc_info=True).
